{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"WakeLockSentinel","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.WakeLockSentinel"],"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Screen_Wake_Lock_API\">Screen Wake Lock API</a></strong></li><li><strong><em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>WakeLockSentinel</code></a></em></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/released\"><code>released</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/type\"><code>type</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance methods</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/release\"><code>release()</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/release_event\"><code>release</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Screen Wake Lock API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/wakeLock\"><code>Navigator.wakelock</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLock\"><code>WakeLock</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard secure\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Secure context:</strong> This feature is available only in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Secure_Contexts\">secure contexts</a> (HTTPS), in some or all <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">supporting browsers</a>.</p></div>\n<p>The <strong><code>WakeLockSentinel</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Screen_Wake_Lock_API\">Screen Wake Lock API</a> provides a handle to the underlying platform wake lock and can be manually released and reacquired. An <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object\"><code>Object</code></a> representing the wake lock is returned via the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLock/request\" title=\"navigator.wakeLock.request()\"><code>navigator.wakeLock.request()</code></a> method.</p>\n<p>An acquired <code>WakeLockSentinel</code> can be released manually via the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/release\" title=\"release()\"><code>release()</code></a> method, or automatically via the platform wake lock. This can happen if the document becomes inactive or looses visibility, if the device is low on power or the user turns on a power save mode. Releasing all <code>WakeLockSentinel</code> instances of a given wake lock type will cause the underlying platform wake lock to be released.</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"88\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"44\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      EventTarget\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"88\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"118\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"88,14 98,9 98,19 88,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" xlink:href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"118\" y=\"0\" width=\"128\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"182\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      WakeLockSentinel\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_properties","title":"Instance properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>This interface provides the following properties.</em></p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"released\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/released\" title=\"released\"><code>released</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns a boolean indicating whether the <code>WakeLockSentinel</code> has been released.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"type\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/type\" title=\"type\"><code>type</code></a> <span title=\"This value may not be changed.\" class=\"badge inline readonly\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      Returns a string representation of the currently acquired <code>WakeLockSentinel</code> type.\n      Return values are:\n    </p>\n    <ul>\n      <li><code>'screen'</code>: A screen wake lock. Prevents devices from dimming or locking the screen.</li>\n    </ul>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"events","title":"Events","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"release\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/release_event\" title=\"release\"><code>release</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Fired when the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/release\" title=\"release()\"><code>release()</code></a> method is called or the wake lock is released by the user agent.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_methods","title":"Instance methods","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"release_2\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel/release\" title=\"release()\"><code>release()</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Releases the <code>WakeLockSentinel</code>, returning a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Promise\"><code>Promise</code></a> that is resolved once the sentinel has been successfully released.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>In this example we create an asynchronous function which requests a <code>WakeLockSentinel</code>. Once acquired we listen for the <code>release</code> event which can be used to give appropriate UI feedback. The sentinel can be acquired or released via appropriate interactions.</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token comment\">// create a reference for the wake lock</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> wakeLock <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">null</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// create an async function to request a wake lock</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">requestWakeLock</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">async</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">try</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    wakeLock <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> navigator<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>wakeLock<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">request</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"screen\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// listen for our release event</span>\n    wakeLock<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"release\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token comment\">// if wake lock is released alter the UI accordingly</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">catch</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>err<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// if wake lock request fails - usually system related, such as battery</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nwakeLockOnButton<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"click\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">requestWakeLock</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\nwakeLockOffButton<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">addEventListener</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"click\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>wakeLock <span class=\"token operator\">!==</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">null</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    wakeLock<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">release</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">then</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=&gt;</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      wakeLock <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">null</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/screen-wake-lock/#the-wakelocksentinel-interface","title":"Screen Wake Lock API"}],"query":"api.WakeLockSentinel"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.WakeLockSentinel"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Instance properties","id":"instance_properties"},{"text":"Events","id":"events"},{"text":"Instance methods","id":"instance_methods"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The WakeLockSentinel interface of the Screen Wake Lock API provides a handle to the underlying platform wake lock and can be manually released and reacquired. An Object representing the wake lock is returned via the navigator.wakeLock.request() method.","popularity":0.0006,"modified":"2023-04-18T13:30:55.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/wakelocksentinel","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/wakelocksentinel/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/d5b200b38608637d835886fb6865ed4b2b5a375b","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"WakeLockSentinel","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WakeLockSentinel","title":"WakeLockSentinel"}],"pageTitle":"WakeLockSentinel - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}